title: Low Carb Custard Recipe
directions: Combine the custard ingredients in a blender or magic bullet and blend until smooth. Pour into two greased 6 oz ramekins or bowls. Preheat the oven to 325 degrees (F). Place your ramekins in a deep pan and place in the oven. Pour hot water up into the deep pan until halfway up the sides of the ramekins. Bake for 30 minutes, or until set. Remove and chill for at least one hour (or overnight) before serving.
Optional: Sprinkle cinnamon on top before eating.
ingredients: 1 packet sugar substitute (splenda, ideal, swerve, etc.)
